transpose to positions considered after 10.Rb1} b6 { Black focuses on developing 
his pieces. Next, Black would like to play ...Bb7 and then ...Qd7.} 10. a3 Bb7 11. 
b4 Qd7 12. Be3 {This bishop is ideally placed on e3, covering the d4-square. So 
before taking any further action on the queenside White decides to develop his bishop.} 
Nd4 { preventing any d3-d4 ideas.} 13. Qd2 {and now after,} (13. f4 f5 {this is 
a typical reaction whenever White plays f2-f4.} 14. Bf2 Nec6 15. Qd2 {and surprisingly 
after} Rae8 {we transpose to a position covered in one the lines below.} ) Nec6 
